### Create a domain

```
Example Request
```

```shell
curl "https://api.example.org/v3/domains" \
  -X POST \
  -H "Authorization: bearer [token]" \
  -H "Content-type: application/json" \
  -d '{
    "name": "example.com",
    "internal": false
  }'
```

```
Example Response
```

```http
HTTP/1.1 201 Created
Content-Type: application/json

<%= yield_content :single_domain %>
```

#### Definition
`POST /v3/domains`

#### Required Parameters

Name     | Type     | Description
-------  | -------  | -----------
**name** | _string_ | Name of the domain.

#### Optional Parameters

Name         | Type      | Description                                                                    | Default
-----------  | --------  | -----------------------------------------------------------------------------  | -------
**stack**    | _string_  | The name of the stack that the domain will use.                             | null
**position** | _integer_ | The order in which the domains are checked during domain auto-detection. | 1
**enabled**  | _boolean_ | Whether or not the domain will be used for staging                          | true
**locked**   | _boolean_ | Whether or not the domain is locked to prevent updating the bits            | false
**metadata.labels** _(experimental)_| [_label object_](#labels) | Labels applied to the domain.
**metadata.annotations** _(experimental)_ | [_annotation object_](#annotations) | Annotations applied to the domain. |

#### Permitted Roles

      |
----- | ---
